added.title: Lil' Dimples
added.description: Thinking it's a way to reconnect with her father, Raven enters a beauty pageant.

added.title: The Real Orangins!
added.description: Robin tries again to tell the real origin story of the Teen Titans.

added.title: The Scoop
added.description: The Titans find it odd when Starfire becomes friends with an ice cream scoop.

added.title: The Laziest
added.description: Gumball and Darwin challenge Dad to a "lazy-off."

added.title: The Man
added.description: It's Granny Jojo's Birthday and she's brought an unexpected guest to dinner. Granny Jojo has brought a boyfriend to her birthday meal and Dad isn't happy about it. He bans Granny JoJo from ever seeing Louis again. When the kids get caught sneaking Granny Jojo out of the house, Dad challenges Louis to a man-off to prove once and for all who is the man of the house?!!

added.title: The Menu
added.description: The prize jewel on the Secret Joyful Burger menu is a mysterious burger, but to order it you need to know its name. When Larry refuses to tell them what it's called, they go to super-sized lengths to discover it.

added.title: The Deal
added.description: When Mom wins Employee of the Month at the Rainbow factory, Richard feels like he is never celebrated for all the work he does at home. Nicole is suspicious of how much he actually does, but when Richard goes on strike, his important role in keeping things under control becomes painfully clear...

added.title: The Choices
added.description: When a typically stressful Watterson family dinner pushes her to the edge of her sanity, Nicole starts reminiscing about the time she met Richard. Might her life have been better if she'd never stopped to talk to her future husband and taken a different path instead?

added.title: Fall Anthology
added.description: In an attempt to finish a school project, Craig remembers some of his favorite Fall moments.

added.title: King of Camping
added.description: The Williams Family goes camping and Craig helps his dad prove he's the King of Camping.

added.title: Brother Builder
added.description: As Craig races against time to build a super important invention, we learn how Craig became such a clever inventor!

added.title: A Tattle Tale
added.description: Craig, Kelsey and JP find themselves stranded on an island of tattle-tales.

added.title: Happy Bouncy Fun Town
added.description: The Bears land in the cheeriest place of all time, but Ice Bear starts to feel out of place.

added.title: Back to Our Regular Time Period
added.description: The Bears find themselves trapped in the wrong time period.

added.title: Bath on the Nile
added.description: The Bears find themselves in an ancient Egyptian spa, but Grizz refuses to take a bath.

added.title: Bubble Fields
added.description: The Bears try to prove to Unica that they can be expert bubble-ologists.

added.title: Who Crashed the RV
added.description: When Squatter Otter finds his new RV destroyed, each bear tells their own version of what happened.

added.title: For a Few Duncans More
added.description: While trying to photocopy his butt on Chef's fancy new copier Duncan accidentally makes an entire other Duncan. Great! This other Duncan can do all the school stuff while the real Duncan chills. But things go badly when the other Duncan decides to copy himself so he can chill too.

added.title: He Who Wears the Clown
added.description: After trying on the nose of a clown Owen learns that this is how clowns are made and he is stuck as a clown until he can trick someone else into asking to try on the nose.

added.title: Us 'R' Toys
added.description: When Chef brings in some old toys from his childhood he, Duncan and Gwen, each get magically sucked into one of the toys and need to find a way to get back into their own bodies.

added.title: Dream Worriers
added.description: Izzy forgets the ending to her most amazing dream of all time, so the kids travel into her mind to find out what happened.

added.title: Grody to the Maximum
added.description: Cody gets a super cool, new t-shirt. It's SO cool that the kids don't even recognize him, so Cody jumps on the chance to leave his old life behind and become popular.

added.title: One Hit Wonder
added.description: Apple & Onion can't bear to work another day in their dead end jobs at the dollar store but as always, money is the issue. If only there was a way they didn't have to worry about money any more.

added.title: A Matter of Pride
added.description: Apple & Onion's jobs have become too demeaning. They decide to put their foots down. It's a matter of pride.

added.title: Eyesore a Sunset
added.description: Art is subjective and Apple and Onion agree to let that get between them.

added.title: For Queen and Country
added.description: Onion has an unexpected and impossible new love interest. Off to England then.

added.title: Petri
added.description: Apple and Onion must get back to their apartment to put the lid on their petri dish.

added.title: Bottomless Ben
added.description: While visiting Carlsbad Caverns National Park, the Tennyson's come across the "Bottomless Pit", a naturally formed pit with no bottom. Ben fights his better judgment to jump in the pit and be the first person to find the bottom, until Kevin 11 shows up and starts to goad Ben into a contest to the bottom of the pit! The natural rivalry is put on hold, however, with the arrival of Breaker One-Nine, who has come to destroy the Caverns!

added.title: Tales from the Omnitrix
added.description: Team Tennyson trade campfire stories in an anthology-style series that pits Ben against his archrival, Kevin 11, and teaches our hero the power of imagination.

added.title: Party Poopers
added.description: Ben completely ignores Gwen when she takes him to a family fun center. Meanwhile, Frightwig pushes Zombozo back into a life of crime after he ends up becoming a party clown. Now, both Ben and Zombozo will have to learn that you shouldn't ignore your friends!

added.title: Wind Some, Lose Some
added.description: At the Mojave Wind Farm in Texas, Max and Gwen plan to set Ben straight on his kooky ideas about how wind works, but when they find the Weatherheads using the towering turbines for their latest nefarious plan, will Ben face facts in time to blow them away?

added.title: Digital Quality
added.description: Ben and Gwen don't want to go to the CD Library. CDs are for old people. Ew. Once Team Tennyson is there, Lord Decibel traps them inside and demands a ransom. Ben and Gwen find Kevin inside on a potentially nefarious quest of his own, but it turns out that Lord Decibel may have already found the item that they so desperately desire.

added.title: Merry Christmas
added.description: When the Rustbucket's A/C goes on the fritz in the middle of the desert, Ben, Max and Gwen take refuge at Holiday Village, an over the top Christmas theme park that seems to appear out of nowhere. The place is run by an evil entity known as Mr. Jingles, who takes Max prisoner because he believes Max is Santa! It's up to Ben and Gwen to free Max and break the spell Mr. Jingles has cast on Holiday Village, freeing others who've been trapped their for years and releasing the theme park.

added.title: Benwolf
added.description: In New Mexico, Max stops to visit an old friend, who's a Navajo Chief. Suddenly, a powerful storm comes out of nowhere. And behind bolts of purple lightning, a Navajo werewolf appears. As Ben battles the werewolf, he appears to be bitten and turns into Benwolf.

added.title: Game Over
added.description: When Ben, as Upgrade, and Gwen get zapped into a Sumo Slammers video game, Ben soon has to deal with Gwen's superior gaming skills, while he also tries to impress his video icon in the game.

added.title: Monster Weather
added.description: Max takes the kids to a drought stricken Chicago to see his favorite golden oldie band perform at a huge music festival. Once there, our heroes cross paths with a deranged weatherman.

added.title: Super Alien Hero Buddy Adventures
added.description: Ben discovers his alien heroes have been ripped off by a lame cartoon and he is not happy. So he sets out to make things right.

added.title: Stakes Part 5: May I Come In?
added.description: Finn, Jake, Marceline, and PB set out to hunt down the Vamps. But who is hunting them?

added.title: Stakes Part 1: Marceline the Vampire Queen
added.description: Finn & Jake hunt for a shadowy predator and Marceline asks Princess Bubblegum for a huge favor.

added.title: Stakes Part 2: Everything Stays
added.description: As the sun rises on her last day, Marceline recalls her long extraordinary life.

added.title: Stakes Part 3: Vamps About
added.description: Five foes from Marceline's past come back to cause trouble for the Land of Ooo.

added.title: Stakes Part 4: Empress Eyes
added.description: When one of her oldest adversaries targets the Ice Kingdom, Marceline rushes to Simon's rescue.

added.title: Beep
added.description: To help combat bummer feelings, Unikitty's installed Bad Vibe detectors throughout the castle. But soon, annoying beeping detectors fill the halls, and they can't find the source of the bad vibes or shut off the sound! It would seem someone's not owning up to being in a bad mood.Will the friends figure out who is secretly a Negative Nancy, or will they lose their mind to beeping madness?

added.title: Delivery Effect
added.description: Unikitty and gang have ordered some delicious Thai food for dinner.  Unfortunately the wait for the delivery is proving too much, time itself seems to have slowed down. In an effort to get the food their faster the gang utilizes Dr. Fox's time machine, which causes big problems and really hurts Father Time's feelings.

added.title: Lazer Tag
added.description: When the Score creeper traps Unikitty and the gang in his laser tag arena the gang must defeat the house team or be imprisoned forever.

added.title: Trapped in Paradise
added.description: Unikitty and the gang have crashed on a fabulous island. It's really nice and no one wants to leave until Richard convinces them that they need to return to the Kingdom and deal with their responsibilities. Unfortunately every attempt to escape the island is sabotaged. Now they must find the culprit to ensure their return home.

added.title: Prank War
added.description: When Master Frown starts a prank war with UniKingdom, the friends are ready to strike back. But Unikitty doesn't really understand pranks, thinking they're too mean. Can the friends help Unikitty comprehend a proper goof and win the prank war with Frown? Or will they be forced to suffer his tricks without retaliation and admit defeat?

added.title: Film Flam
added.description: A sleazy director arrives in Townsville to make a film about the Powerpuff Girls. But this Hollywood type wants more out of Townsville than an Oscar-winning film.

added.title: The Powerpuff Girls: A Documentary/Girls Gone Mild
added.description: The Powerpuff Girls a Documentary: A film student attempts to do a documentary on the Powerpuff Girls and learns catching these superheroes at rest is harder than he thought./Girls Gone Mild: When Parents Against Powerpuffs tell the girls that their superheroics are becoming too imitable, the girls must hold back on fighting crime.

added.title: The Headsucker's Moxy/Equal Fights
added.description: The Headsucker's Moxy: There's a mysterious villain in town who's sucking pertinent information from the brains of powerful people and committing crimes. How do the girls trap this sucker before his next victim is drained?/Equal Fights: When the girls try to catch a local female villain, she tells them that as women they've got to stick together. It's up to the women of Townsville to teach our heroines the true meaning of equality.

added.title: Get Back Jojo
added.description: Mojo goes back in time to try and stop the Professor from having the inspiration for the perfect little girls. Little does he know that in doing so he provides just the spark the young Professor needs.

added.title: Moral Decay/Meet the Beat Alls
added.description: Moral Decay: When Bubbles loses a tooth, she gets a shiny coin under her pillow the next day. Buttercup sees a gold mine in the mouths of Townsville's criminal element./Meet the Beat Alls: Mojo, Him, Princess and Fuzzy band together to form the Bad Four, a criminal supergroup out to destroy the Powerpuff Girls. Everything is going great until Mojo meets Moko Jono and falls in love.

added.title: Save the Date
added.description: Ms. Keane is nervous about a first date.

added.title: Can't Buy Love
added.description: When Morbucks falls in love, she finds the first thing money can't buy.

added.title: Largo
added.description: When a mysterious rain cloud plagues Townsville, Bubbles learns things aren't what they seem.

added.title: Blundercup
added.description: Buttercup is knocked off-kilter by a mysterious force.

added.title: Ragnarock and Roll
added.description: When an ancient prophecy spells doom for Townsville, the girls must race to stop it.

added.title: Private Lake
added.description: When the local lake is overcrowded with tourists, the Bears have fun at Charlie's private lake.

added.title: Lunch with Tabes
added.description: When Tabes's lunch gets stolen, Tabes launches a full investigation to find the culprit.

added.title: Road Trip
added.description: Chloe and the Bears take a road trip to see a meteor shower. Ice Bear, the only one licensed to drive, is put in charge, which becomes harder than he thought.

added.title: Summer Love
added.description: Panda goes on a mission to return a lost phone to the girl of his dreams.

added.title: The Kitty
added.description: After a mishap in the forest, the Bears lose their own home to dangerous animals.

added.title: Bucky and the Howl
added.description: After Clarence learns Sumo's in the school musical, he joins up and enthusiastically promotes the show. On opening night with a packed house, stage fright takes hold of Sumo and he runs off leaving Clarence to go on alone.

added.title: Capture the Flag
added.description: Water balloon fights, warring factions and the risk of jail time, everything is on the line when Clarence and friends play the biggest game of capture the flag yet! Everyone wants to take home the crown, and the power to control the neighborhood's juice boxes.

added.title: Cloris
added.description: When Clarence befriends an aging woman at the local retirement home, he's determined to remind her of her old self in order to convert the grumpy granny to his fun loving ways.

added.title: Belson's Backpack
added.description: After an accidental backpack swap, Clarence discovers that Belson is hiding an artistic side and attempts to foster Belson's creativity.

added.title: Motel
added.description: Following an insect mishap Clarence's house needs to be fumigated forcing Mary, Chad, and Clarence into a motel. In the meantime, Clarence and Chad learn a bit about responsibility while Mary contemplates a life of letting go.

added.title: Uncle Cupid
added.description: Cupid, too lonely to perform his Valentine's Day duties, comes to Uncle Grandpa for help.

added.title: Bottom Bag
added.description: After receiving a new bag friend, Belly Bag has to realize its nefarious intentions to completely replace Belly Bag and stop it before it's too late.

added.title: Watermelon Gag
added.description: When Uncle Grandpa gets a watermelon stuck in his mouth, he is unable to ask for help and people interpret it as a comedy routine. As Uncle Grandpa's popularity rises, his friendships and morale suffer.

added.title: Uncle Grandpa Babies
added.description: When the President calls in the Uncle Grandpa babies, they have to act quickly and use their special baby powers to defuse a missile.

added.title: Birdman
added.description: When Birdman makes the RV's attic his new home, Uncle Grandpa and the gang must figure out a way to make him leave before they're all driven crazy.

added.title: Into the Dark
added.description: When Cole investigates a mysterious visitor, the ninja aren't sure what to believe. Cole is frustrated with this lack of team support, until Princess Vania reveals a secret entrance that leads to an underground mine beneath Shintaro - where the city's dark secrets are held.

added.title: The Worst Rescue Ever
added.description: The ninja attempt to rescue Cole, but the bickering of his fellow prisoners, the Geckles and Munce, alerts the Skull Sorcerer, and soon the ninja are prisoners too.

added.title: The Two Blades
added.description: In order to escape the Skull Sorcerer's chain-gang, the ninja must convince the Munce and Geckles to put aside their distrust and work together… by promising them something they may not be able to deliver -- The Blades of Deliverance!

added.title: Queen of the Munce
added.description: Jay, Nya and Lloyd are led deep into the Mines of Shintaro by Murt, who brings them back to the Munce "Home- Cave" - a settlement deep in the mountain. There, complications arise when they meet the Munce Queen, Murtessa, who takes a liking to Jay.

added.title: Trial By Mino
added.description: Separated from the others, Kai and Zane discover a party of Geckles who suspect them of being in league with the Skull Sorcerer, and bring them before their leader, Chancellor Gulch, who subjects them to a "Trial-By-Mino."

added.title: Ben sin fondo
added.description: Los Tennyson se topan con un "pozo sin fondo": un pozo formado naturalmente, que carece de fondo. Ben se debate internamente si debe entrar o no, ihasta que llega Kevin 11 y empieza a incitarlo a hacer una carrera hacia abajo!

added.title: Historias del Omnitrix
added.description: El Equipo Tennyson comparte historias de fogón en un episodio estilo antología, que enfrenta a Ben contra Kevin 11, su archirrival, y le enseña el poder de la imaginación a nuestro héroe.

added.title: Aguafiestas
added.description: Ben ignora completamente a Gwen cuando van a un centro de diversión familiar. Mientras tanto, Frightwig empuja a Zombozo a una vida de crímenes luego de que este termina convertido en un payaso para fiestas. iAhora, Zombozo y Ben deben aprender que no deberías ignorar a tus amigos!

added.title: Dales aire y dejalos salir
added.description: En la granja eólica de Mojave, Gwen y Max intentan enderezar las locas ideas de Ben sobre como funciona el viento. Pero cuando encuentran a los Climáticos usando las imponentes turbinas para sus viles objetivos, ¿podrá Ben aceptar los hechos a tiempo para derrotarlos?

added.title: Bip
added.description: Para ayudar a combatir los sentimientos negativos, Unikitty ha instalado detectores de malas vibraciones en todo el castillo. Pero pronto, la molesta alarma de los detectores llena los pasillos, iy nadie puede encontrar la fuente de las malas vibraciones ni apagar el sonido! Parece que alguien no está reconociendo su propio mal humor. ¿Se darán cuenta los amigos de quién es la persona que guarda su negatividad en secreto, o perderán la cabeza por la locura de la alarma?

added.title: Efecto Entrega
added.description: Unikitty y su banda pidieron una deliciosa comida tailandesa para la cena. Por desgracia, la espera para la entrega se está haciendo demasiado larga y hasta el tiempo parece pasar más lento. En un esfuerzo por conseguir la comida más rápido, la banda utiliza la máquina del tiempo de la Dra. Fox, lo cual causa graves problemas y hiere profundamente los sentimientos del Padre Tiempo.

added.title: Lazer Tag
added.description: Cuando un villano atrapa a Unikitty y a la banda en su campo de disparos láser, deben derrotar al equipo local o quedar atrapados para siempre.

added.title: Por unos Duncans mas
added.description: Mientras trataba de fotocopiar su trasero en la nueva y elegante fotocopiadora del Chef, Duncan accidentalmente hace otro Duncan completo. iExcelente! Este otro Duncan puede hacer todas las cosas de la escuela mientras el verdadero Duncan se enfría. Pero las cosas van mal cuando el otro Duncan decide copiarse a sí mismo para poder relajarse también.

added.title: En la Oscuridad
added.description: La princesa Vania revela una entrada secreta que conduce a una mina subterránea bajo Shintaro donde se guardan los oscuros secretos de la ciudad.

added.title: Quiero Ser Payaso
added.description: Después de probarse la nariz de un payaso, Owen se entera de que así es como se hacen los payasos y está atrapado como un payaso hasta que puede engañar a otra persona para que le pida probarse la nariz.

added.title: Atrapados en el paraiso
added.description: Unikitty y la banda aterrizaron de emergencia en una isla fabulosa. Todo es muy bonito y nadie quiere irse hasta que Richard los convence de que tienen que volver al Reino y asumir sus responsabilidades. Por desgracia, alguien sabotea cada intento de escapar de la isla. Ahora deben encontrar al culpable para asegurar su regreso a casa.

added.title: El Peor Rescate de la Historia
added.description: Los Ninjas intentan rescatar a Cole, pero las discusiones entre prisioneros alertan al Hechicero Calavera, y hace prisioneros a los otros Ninjas.

added.title: Somos Juguetes
added.description: Cuando el Chef trae algunos juguetes viejos de su infancia, él, Duncan y Gwen, cada uno es absorbido mágicamente por uno de los juguetes y necesitan encontrar una manera de volver a sus propios cuerpos.

added.title: Guerra de Bromas
added.description: Cuando Master Frown comienza una guerra de bromas con el Unireino, los amigos están listos para contraatacar. Pero Unikitty no entiende bien las bromas, y piensa que tienen demasiada maldad. ¿Pueden los amigos ayudar a Unikitty a comprender una buena broma y ganar la guerra contra Frown? ¿O se verán obligados a sufrir sus bromas sin represalias y admitir la derrota?

added.title: Suenos Problematicos
added.description: Izzy olvida el final de su sueño más asombroso de todos los tiempos, por lo que los niños viajan a su mente para descubrir qué sucedió.

added.title: Las Dos Espadas
added.description: Para escapar de la prisión del Hechicero Calavera, los Ninjas debe convencer a los Munces y a Geckles de que dejen de discutir y trabajen juntos.

added.title: La Reina de los Munces
added.description: Jay, Nya y Lloyd son guiados entre las minas de Shintaro por Murt, quien los lleva de vuelta a la Cueva de los Munces. A la Reina Munce le gusta Jay.

added.title: Grody al Maximo
added.description: Cody recibe una camiseta nueva y genial. Es TAN genial que los niños ni siquiera lo reconocen, así que Cody aprovecha la oportunidad de dejar atrás su antigua vida y volverse popular.

added.title: Juicio de Mino
added.description: Un grupo de Geckles creen que Kai y Zane están aliados con el Hechicero Calavera y los llevan con su líder, quien los somete a un juicio por Mino…

added.title: Splash Zone
added.description: Mayor Foghorn Leghorn hires The Looney Builders to build a giant water slide for Looneyburg's waterpark. He keeps adding onto the design with the support of Bugs until problems arise.

added.title: Ice Creamed
added.description: It's Taz's birthday, so The Looney Builders build him a huge ice cream sundae. Porky worries about making a mistake and delays the build causing the ice cream to start to melt.

added.title: That Ol' Time Rock Rolls!/Make Like a Banana and Split
added.description: When Big Old Boulder rolls down the hill towards the museum, Berta needs the Mechas help to keep it stable./It's Food Day in Pretty Big City, but the Mechas need to help when the banana atop the banana split statue is not split!

added.title: Magnet Mayhem/Stop That Train
added.description: The magnet crane at the construction site accidentally turns on, sucking up all the metal, including the Mecha Builders!/Roof is delivering eggs to Marwyn at the Train Station, that is, until the train pulls into the station and can't stop!

removed.title: Un Dia Peludo
removed.description: Bridgette dona su cabello a una organización benéfica que fabrica pelucas para gatos sin pelo y ahora algunos compañeros quieren hacer lo mismo. Pero su búsqueda de una peluca perfecta los lleva a longitudes extrañas y peligrosas.

removed.title: Fiesta en el Calabozo
removed.description: Cole, Wu y la Princesa Vania conocen a un grupo de sobrevivientes llamados los de abajo, ellos cuentan cómo terminaron en "Lo más profundo".

removed.title: El Dragon Grief-Bringer
removed.description: Nya y Kai, quienes se han convertido en los líderes de los Munces y Geckles, intentan unirlos para derrotar a su enemigo mutuo, el Hechicero Calavera.

removed.title: El Hechicero Calavera
removed.description: Separado de los demás, Cole debe encontrar su camino a la superficie para advertir al Rey Vangelis sobre el peligroso Hechicero Calavera.

removed.title: El Reves del Hambre
removed.description: Owen tiene un percance mientras horneaba un pastel al revés y es transportado a un mundo al revés donde se ve obligado a burlarse de sí mismo para recuperar su pastel.

removed.title: El Camino en el Calabozo
removed.description: En su misión de derrotar al Rey Vangelis, Cole, Wu y Vania unen fuerzas con "Los de abajo" para encontrar una forma de salir del fondo de la montaña.

removed.title: Tuba o No Tuba
removed.description: La clase intenta ayudar al Chef a lograr su sueño de unirse a la banda de tuba más famosa del mundo, Tubalicious, solo para arrepentirse cuando se dan cuenta de cuánto lo extrañarán.

removed.title: La Gran Caida
removed.description: Este episodio relata cómo Cole, la princesa Vania y el maestro Wu caen por un túnel aparentemente interminable, dentro de la montaña de Shintaro.

removed.title: Y Donde Esta el Guacamayo?
removed.description: Mientras intenta defender su estatus de jugador de élite, Chef usa un antiguo código de trampa que da vida a un avatar peligroso.

removed.title: Be Afraid of the Dark
removed.description: Ben travels into space to thwart Ghostfreak's diabolical plans. But is he hero enough to take on the Mummy, Werewolf and Frankenstein?

removed.title: The Visitor
removed.description: A mysterious alien named Xylene shows up and wants to return the Omnitrix to its rightful owner, Grandpa Max!

removed.title: Under Wraps
removed.description: When Ben and Gwen are sent to a farm to learn the value of hard work, what they really learn is that an evil alien mummy has arrived on Earth.

removed.title: The Unnaturals
removed.description: Ben learns that evil robots have replaced all the kids at the Little League World Series. And now they want to replace the President of the USA!

removed.title: The Return
removed.description: Ghostfreak has returned! And he has brought a Mummy, Werewolf and Frankenstein like aliens with him to help him shroud the Earth in darkness.

removed.title: Dino Fright
removed.description: George P. Mandrake hires The Looney Builders to build a T. Rex fossil. It's Tweety's job to place the bones with his crane, but his fear of the big dino affects his ability to get the job done.

removed.title: Picture Perfect Park Party/Sun Block
removed.description: Hero Celebration Day is finishing with a slideshow of everyday heroes, that is, until the projector screen rips./Pretty Big City is cooling off with an ice slide in the park, but the situation gets slippery when the slide starts melting.

removed.title: Snow Cap
removed.description: Pauleen Penguin hires The Looney Builders to build her a home in Looneyburg. Lola soon discovers they got the design wrong and the crew has to make adjustments.

removed.title: Roll Chickens, Roll!/Ramp Up, Up, And Away
removed.description: Farmer MacBarm is hosting the Sunny Field Farm Chicken Roll, but the race gets off to a slow start when the chickens don't roll./Ranger Nat can't wait to see Pinecone's Comet, that is, until his telescope falls to the bottom of a cliff.

removed.title: Rekoil
removed.description: As Team Tennyson fights to stop Dr. Animo from raiding an animal shelter, Ben faces one villain more than he bargained for, King Koil, now Animo's pet.

removed.title: De-Fanged!
removed.description: Team Tennyson travels to the new Laser Town VR, but when Kevin cheats his way to the top, Ben must team up with former champ Fang if he is going to defeat his souped-up rival.

removed.title: Mock 10
removed.description: Ben, Kevin and La Grange find themselves stuck 'outside of time' after the latter hijacks a supersonic train with a faulty engine, forcing the trio to team up and slow down.

removed.title: Buktu The Future
removed.description: After Tim Buktu's live stream is mysteriously cut short, Team Tennyson must attempt a rescue mission and break inside the highly confidential Area 55 in order to save him.

removed.title: Players of the Lost Park
removed.description: When Team Tennyson visits Raspberry Park for some R & R, they get more than they bargained for. What they think are innocent games of chance are a revenge plot by Zombozo to steal the Rustbuggy and rob Team Tennyson!

removed.title: Craig of the Campus
removed.description: Craig is dragged along on a college tour, but quickly finds himself chasing after a creek legend.

removed.title: Wheels Collide
removed.description: Craig tries to bring together the fastest kids in the Creek, and accidentally creates a rivalry between the 10 Speeds and the Roller Derby Kids.

removed.title: The Upside of Hunger
removed.description: Owen has a mishap while baking an upside-down cake and is transported to an upside-down world where he is forced to outwit himself in order to get his cake back.

removed.title: Tu Ba or Not Tu Ba
removed.description: The class tries to help Chef achieve his dream of joining the world's most famous Tuba Band, Tubalicious, only to regret it when they realize how much they'll miss him.

removed.title: Dude Where's Macaw
removed.description: While trying to defend his elite gamer status Chef uses an old cheat code that brings a dangerous avatar to life.

removed.title: Wiggin' Out
removed.description: Bridgette donates her hair to a charity that makes wigs for hairless cats and now some classmates want to do the same. But their quest for perfect wig hair drives them to weird and dangerous lengths.

removed.title: Fire in the Hole
removed.description: Duncan cooks up a nuclear hot sauce to mess with Chef, but accidentally summons Terry Spice, King of the Underworld!
